        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 5:36PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM EDT/436 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of
strong thunderstorms over Signal Mountain, or near Chattanooga,
moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Jasper, Signal Mountain, Walden, Whitwell, Kimball,
Ridgeside, Fairmount, Red Bank, and Powells Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
